'''''Wordly Wise 3000''''' is an American series of workbooks published by Educators Publishing Service for the teaching of [[English orthography|spelling]] and [[English vocabulary|vocabulary]]. Books A through C (for grades 2–4) introduce 300 words and books 1–9 (grades 4–12) 3,000 words, all with exercises.<ref>{{cite book|title=Closing the literacy gap|author=Gunning, Thomas G.|page=53|year=2006|publisher=[[Allyn & Bacon]]|isbn=978-0-205-45626-0}}</ref> As well as spelling and meaning, the books cover the [[etymology]] and stories behind the words discussed.<ref>{{cite book|title=Making minds less well educated than our own|authorlink=Roger Schank|author=Schank, Roger C.|page=51|year=2004|publisher=[[Routledge]]|isbn=978-0-8058-4878-6}}</ref> The series is popular amongst [[Homeschooling|home schoolers]]<ref>{{cite book|title=The Big Book of Home Learning: Teen and Adult|authorlink=Mary Pride|author=Pride, Mary|page=95|year=1991 |publisher=[[Crossway Books]]|isbn=978-0-89107-550-9}}</ref> and [[Christian school|Christian educators]].<ref>{{cite book|title=100 Top Picks for Homeschool Curriculum: Choosing the Right Educational Philosophy for Your Child's Learning Style|author=Duffy, Cathy|page=199|year=2005|publisher=[[B&H Publishing Group]]|isbn=978-0-8054-3138-4}}</ref> In 2017 Wordly Wise partnered with [[Quizlet]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2017/08/23/quizlet-a-popular-study-app-faces-a-moment-of-truth.html|title=Popular study app Quizlet faces a moment of truth as a new school year begins|author=Lora Kolodny|publisher=[[CNBC]]|date=August 23, 2017|accessdate=May 2, 2018}}</ref>

